objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: Welcome to hell
objects.text:
Before me things create were none,
save things Eternal, and eternal I endure.
All hope abandon ye who enter here.

objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: Secure the base
objects.text:
Our bridge to the north has been discovered! 
We can expect attack from two sides... unless you find something to block this path.

objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: Secure the base
objects.text: Great job! Now, when you've stopped the attack, we can take care of more prosaic matters. Like food...

objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: Reach the temple
objects.text:
We cannot stay here forever. 
We're running out of food, with no hope for new supplies. Old diary left by the previous expedition mentions some kind of temple, hidden in the valey to the north. Local tribes use temples as a kind of granaries. If you want to surive, you must reach it! But remember, staying away from the base can have a terrible influence on ones mind. So take the base with you, as you move forward.

objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: Survivor
objects.text:
Searching the ruins you've found a note:
 "I'm moving north, there are supplies! - Bob"

objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: Survivor
objects.text:
You've met a survivor from the previous expedition.
Bob tells you about some ancient construction to the East. He doesn't know it's purpose but it's heavily guarded. He also mentions a useful method of hiding in the IKEA Bunker when there is no other shelter during attacks.

objects.name: BasicJournalEntry
objects.title: %1 died
objects.text: %1 is now in the better place.
